02/09/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The government on Monday (September 1st) urged displaced ethnic Serbs to return to the country.
Officials held a ground-breaking ceremony for construction of a collection centre for displaced Serbs willing to return and restart their lives in Kosovo.
The government is committed to creating a better life for all Kosovo citizens through such projects, Prime Minister Hashim Thaci said at the ceremony.
The centre, near Pristina, will be able to accommodate 60 families.
(Koha ditore, Zeri, Lajm - 02/09/08;
RTK, Telegrafi - 01/09/08)
